HEADWORD: Diphenyl
<hw>Di*phe"nyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>phenyl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
white crystalline substance, <chform>C6H5.C6H5</chform>, obtained by
leading benzene through a heated iron tube. It consists of two benzene
or phenyl radicals united.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

